-- MOVES-Smith & Williamson adds John Anderson to fixed income team as partner
-- 
-- Wed Jul 16, 2014 09:40AM EDT
-- None



July 16 (Reuters) - UK-based investment management company Smith & Williamson Investment Management LLP said it added John Anderson to its fixed income team as partner.

Anderson will join Smith & Williamson on July 23. He will manage the Fixed Interest Trust, one of the oldest UK retail corporate bond funds, launched in 1995. The company said Anderson had 30 years' experience, including nine years as head of fixed interest at Rensburg Sheppards Investment Management.